<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Terracotta Watering Pots for Vacation Watering</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    Vacation watering isn’t about automation — it’s about predictability.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most gardeners, the best terracotta watering pots are sealed, unglazed pots sized to last the full absence period while delivering slow, consistent moisture.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Leaving plants unattended is where watering systems fail most often. Too little water stresses plants. Too much creates different problems.
  </p>
  <p>
    Terracotta watering pots (ollas) work because they release water gradually based on soil moisture — but only if sized and set up correctly.
  </p>
</header>

